      "name": "Velocity field validation via PIV comparison",
      "description": "Simulated velocity fields compared to particle image velocimetry (PIV) measurements in the impeller passage and volute. Spatial RMS deviation 6.8% of peak velocity. Uncertainty from laser sheet thickness, seeding density, and rotational phase jitter quantified using GUM framework.",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/morrison/uq/uq-piv-velocity-gum"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/validation/vr-03-hemolysis-index",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index (RH) comparison against in vitro blood damage data",
      "description": "Computed relative hemolysis index (RH) compared to in vitro hemolysis measurements from standardized ASTM F1841 protocol across 5 flow-speed operating points. All 5 operating points yield RH < 1 relative to predicate device. Inherent variability in blood sample donor-to-donor response, hematocrit variation, and temperature fluctuations during in vitro testing was assessed qualitatively by the assessment team based on published literature ranges; no structured probabilistic UQ model was constructed for this result given the complexity of biological variability characterization at MRL 2."
